com.zendesk.sdk.network.impl

Class ZendeskHelpCenterProvider

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.zendesk.sdk.network.impl.ZendeskHelpCenterProvider
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    HelpCenterProvider

    public class ZendeskHelpCenterProvider
extends Object
implements HelpCenterProvider
    Provider used to retrieve data from a Help Center instance.

    Currently the following models can be retrieved

    • Category

    Content will be fetched in the best possible Locale for this device.

        public void getArticlesForLabels(String[] labels,
                        ZendeskCallback<List<SearchArticle>> callback)
        Description copied from interface: HelpCenterProvider
        Fetch a list of articles for the given labels.

        Note that an article must have all labels to be matched.

        Deprecated. Use HelpCenterProvider.listArticles(com.zendesk.sdk.model.helpcenter.ListArticleQuery, com.zendesk.sdk.network.impl.ZendeskCallback) with a ListArticleQuery that specifies label names.

        Specified by:
        getArticlesForLabels in interface HelpCenterProvider
        Parameters:
        labels - The array of labels to match articles against
        callback - The callback which will be called upon a successful or an erroneous response.

      • getArticle

        public void getArticle(Long articleId,
              ZendeskCallback<Article> callback)
        Description copied from interface: HelpCenterProvider
        This method returns a single article from a Help Center instance based on the articleId provided

        This method will also sideload users so that there is a User model available for the author of the article
        See: Article.getAuthor()

        For more information on Side-Loading

        Specified by:
        getArticle in interface HelpCenterProvider
        Parameters:
        articleId - the identifier to be used to retrieve an article from a Help Center instance
        callback - the callback that is invoked when a request has either completed successfully or has errors
